did.abstract: This collection is an inventory of the yearbooks, course catalogs (with related supplements), academic journals, alumni newsletters, view books, registration booklets and other miscellany published by WestConn.

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: Most yearbooks and catalogs were maintained as serials in the catalog.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p:
Published citations should take the following form:
Identification of item, date (if known); The Western Connecticut State University Yearbooks and Catalogs; RG008.1; box number; folder number; Western Connecticut State University

bioghist.head: Historical/Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Western Connecticut State University is a public state university in Danbury, Connecticut. It was founded in 1903 as the Danbury Normal School and is known as WestConn, Western and WCSU. It began as a teacher's college and has evolved to include arts and sciences, business, nursing, music performance, and social work.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: While it is difficult to determine if this collection includes all the catalogs, yearbooks and other related University publications of this kind, it provides a fairly comprehensive assemblage. Issues of the yearbook that the archive does not own are indicated in the scope note for that series.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Danbury Teacher's Quarterly (1941) The students of Danbury State Teacher's College produced this literary journal. Only one issue exists in the Archives.

The WasteCann-(1987) It was an "underground" publication that served as a backlash against university president Stephen Feldman and his administrative staff. Hostile words along with the characterization of President Feldman as Adolf Hitler expressed the feelings of this publication. The author, or authors, of this publication is still unknown.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Clio- (1973-present) This publication is published by the students of the History Department. It began as a quarterly journal, but in 1986 became an annual publication.

odd.head: General
odd.p: The folder originally listed September 1974. It is unclear wether the September issue is missing or the folder was initially mislabeled.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Conatus-(1960-present) This is the literary journal for the university. It was originally published bi-annually, but in 1971 it became an annual publication. The publication includes poetry, essays, short stories, and artwork.

Black & White Journal for the arts, Spring 2010, no. 3

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Courier-(1954-1960) This was the literary journal produced by the students between 1954-1960. It began as an extension of the student newspaper The Supplement. Starting in 1960, the journal was renamed Conatus.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Conjunction-(1994-1997) This bi-annual publication was produced by students of the English Department.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Prisma-(1986-present). The students of the Art Department began this annual publication to exhibit their work with detailed photographs. This collection is incomplete and has several gaps.

odd.head: General
odd.p: Arts magazine published by the Art Department at WCSU.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Smoke Signals-(1957-1973) This was the official student handbook of the college. Published annually by the Cooperative Government Association (later the Student Government Association). The title reflects the fact the athletic teams were known as the Indians. It stopped publication in the mid 1970s when the school changed the name to the Colonials.
Memorial Hall Magazine, (c.a. 1964) This magazine was published to illustrate the different kinds of events and activities that took place in Memorial Hall. We have only one issue.
The Pennington (1935). One issue which contains names of faculty, class officers, seniors, clubs and officers, Student Council Officers (1932-1935), and "News from Class Members" (alumni).

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Social Science Journal-(1995-present) As the title suggests, this annual publication is published by the students of the Social Science Department.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Western Economic Journal-(1985-1993) This annual publication was published by the students of the Economic Club.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Western Scholar-(1998-2007) This annual publication, produced by students, serves as the forum where ideas and opinions can be heard.
